summaries.short: It’s the most wonderful time of the year, for crafting! Kyndal, Sierra, and James create delectable platters of holiday desserts before two merry Craftestants turn mantles into festive masterpieces.
summaries.full: It’s the most wonderful time of the year, for crafting! For their Quick Craft, Kyndal, Sierra, and James set out to find the perfect ingredients to create festive holiday dessert platters. Next, two merry Craftestants incorporate a little piece of home into their handiwork while turning mantles into holiday masterpieces. Guest judge Rosanna Pansino is back to light up Craftopia with her bubbly baker’s spirit.

summaries.short: Julianne, Cooper, and Iva race against the clock to dream up special holiday countdown calendars before two of these talented crafters tackle life-sized holiday window displays.
summaries.full: Julianne, Cooper, and Iva race against the clock to dream up one-of-a-kind holiday countdown calendars that’ll keep the judges smiling for days. And since nothing says "holiday spirit" quite like whimsical window displays, next, two talented crafters tackle this tradition with their very own storefront designs. Wrap god Alton DuLaney drops in to help Toya and James bring one extra lucky Craftestant some majorly good tidings.

summaries.short: Adalyn, Sasha, and Sabrina transform plain paper-mache pinatas into monstrous creations before two of these 11-year-olds get the chance to turn ordinary dollhouses into miniature haunted abodes.
summaries.full: Adalyn, Sasha, and Sabrina transform boring paper-mache pinatas into terrifying monstrous creations before the Craft Master Challenge finds two of these 11-year-olds turning ordinary dollhouses into creepified haunted abodes. Anjelika Temple brings the fear factor to the judges’ panel as they make some bloodcurdling decisions.

summaries.short: Nigel, Tiffany, and Cheyenne hope to get ahead of the challenge with their wow-worthy wigs before crafting chic looks with candy.
summaries.full: After a hair-raising quick challenge leaves Nigel, Tiffany, and Cheyenne wigging out, the Craftestants must create chic candy-inspired looks to impress innovative costume designer Diego Montoya if they want a shot at $10,000 prize - and the Craftophia.

summaries.short: Kaya, Angel, and Erin spook the judges with Halloween-themed mobiles before the two creepiest crafters design light-up costumes too scary to wear.
summaries.full: 15-year-old Californians Kaya, Angel, and Erin spook the judges with Halloween-inspired mobiles before taking their shot at a Craft Master Challenge so wicked it’ll give you head-to-toe chills. As the two creepiest Craftestants construct haunting costumes with a light-up twist, Anjelika Temple returns to help Toya and James decide whose ghoulish getup is truly electrifying.

summaries.short: It’s dog-gone spooky as Ashley, Sean, and Edgar outfit a trio of canine companions before decking themselves out for a spooky split-personality costume challenge.
summaries.full: It’s dog-gone spooky as Ashley, Sean, and Edgar create “pawsome” costumes for some very special canine guests. Then, the trio must create double the daring looks for renowned stylist Anthony Elle.

summaries.short: Chuk, Suhani, and Lily get their hands “slime-y” with a tantalizing Quick Craft before creating life-size doll boxes.
summaries.full: Chuk, Suhani, and Lily have their work cut out for them with a sticky Quick Craft inspired by guest judge Karina Garcia, the “Slime Queen.” Using Karina’s favorite gooey ingredient, our crafters whip up fake food that looks good enough to eat. The two top chefs then tackle a daunting challenge: create life-size doll boxes that tell a story about who they are.

summaries.short: Ready, set, craft. On Craftopia, the ultimate kids' competition series hosted by LaurDIY, crafters meet larger-than-life challenges.
summaries.full: Ready, set, craft. On Craftopia, the ultimate kids' competition series hosted by LaurDIY, crafters meet larger-than-life challenges.
